1
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:07,261
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,331 --> 00:00:08,831
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,031 --> 00:00:14,331
Apparently, this was in my things
when I was adopted.

4
00:00:17,671 --> 00:00:21,641
Your birth mom would recognize you
if she saw this picture, right?

5
00:00:22,611 --> 00:00:24,341
Yes, I guess so.

6
00:00:31,991 --> 00:00:33,051
Mom!

7
00:00:33,751 --> 00:00:35,861
- Gosh, you scared me.
- Come out here, quick!

8
00:00:35,921 --> 00:00:36,921
- Why?
- Hurry!

9
00:00:36,991 --> 00:00:38,761
- What is it? What's wrong with her?
- Just a second.

10
00:00:38,831 --> 00:00:39,831
Seriously, what's gotten into you?

11
00:01:05,521 --> 00:01:06,921
- For goodness' sake.
- Hurry up.

12
00:01:06,991 --> 00:01:07,991
(Episode 23)

13
00:01:08,151 --> 00:01:11,191
Mom, how does Auntie look?
It's her first official day,

14
00:01:11,261 --> 00:01:14,031
so I styled her to have
that powerful CEO vibe.

15
00:01:14,431 --> 00:01:17,031
- Is that what this was about?
- So, what do you think?

16
00:01:18,671 --> 00:01:21,901
Dong Suk, you look so elegant.
Really classy.

17
00:01:22,601 --> 00:01:23,601
You think so?

18
00:01:24,071 --> 00:01:28,441
- Won't her boyfriend be floored?
- He already is.

19
00:01:29,241 --> 00:01:31,141
Come on, you guys.

20
00:01:31,281 --> 00:01:35,381
Auntie, what's the big deal?
Why so secretive about him?

21
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:39,521
What, is this some kind of
forbidden romance?

22
00:01:40,291 --> 00:01:41,291
What?

23
00:01:41,621 --> 00:01:44,061
What's with that look?
That's super suspicious.

24
00:01:45,461 --> 00:01:46,461
Don't tell me.

25
00:01:47,261 --> 00:01:49,161
What? What is it?

26
00:01:49,861 --> 00:01:51,301
Auntie, don't tell me...

27
00:01:52,031 --> 00:01:53,731
You're not dating a married man,
are you?

28
00:01:53,931 --> 00:01:55,171
Hey! Seriously...

29
00:01:55,171 --> 00:01:57,501
Stop talking nonsense and get ready.
We're leaving together.

30
00:01:58,141 --> 00:01:59,971
Why?
Why are you leaving with Eun Bin?

31
00:02:01,041 --> 00:02:02,941
- Oh, it's...
- Well...

32
00:02:02,941 --> 00:02:06,051
I'm also going to my part-time job.
Right, Auntie?

33
00:02:06,111 --> 00:02:08,881
That's right. Our shifts start
around the same time,

34
00:02:08,951 --> 00:02:10,221
so we decided to head out together.

35
00:02:11,751 --> 00:02:15,291
Oh, Dong Suk. Is Dr. Gong's family
coming tomorrow?

36
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:18,391
Yes, my father invited them,

37
00:02:19,391 --> 00:02:21,661
but I'm not sure if all of them
will be able to make it.

38
00:02:22,031 --> 00:02:24,501
What do you mean?
Is there a reason they wouldn't?

39
00:02:25,631 --> 00:02:26,671
No.

40
00:02:27,171 --> 00:02:29,471
I hope they all come.

41
00:02:30,401 --> 00:02:31,401
Right.

42
00:02:31,741 --> 00:02:34,271
You two should get going.
Eun Bin, come on, you'll be late.

43
00:02:35,741 --> 00:02:37,281
- Get your things.
- Okay.

44
00:02:41,311 --> 00:02:43,121
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

45
00:02:43,181 --> 00:02:44,251
Jeong Han...

46
00:02:50,091 --> 00:02:51,191
Yes, Councilor Hwang.

47
00:02:53,061 --> 00:02:55,191
Of course.
I haven't forgotten our appointment.

48
00:02:55,501 --> 00:02:56,661
I'll see you shortly.

49
00:02:57,861 --> 00:03:01,201
Yes, I'll be coming alone.
All right.

50
00:03:03,071 --> 00:03:04,101
What was that?

51
00:03:06,471 --> 00:03:08,471
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

52
00:03:10,881 --> 00:03:11,881
Jeong Han.

53
00:03:14,651 --> 00:03:16,421
Oh, boy.

54
00:03:18,081 --> 00:03:19,121
Hey!

55
00:03:19,491 --> 00:03:21,791
Is he meeting Councilor Hwang alone?

56
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:23,121
Come on. No way.

57
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:25,491
He'll probably ask us
to come along later.

58
00:03:26,861 --> 00:03:28,731
Right? You really think so?

59
00:03:29,061 --> 00:03:31,661
Yes. The fact that he came here
to work with you guys...

60
00:03:31,731 --> 00:03:33,331
means he's already forgiven you.

61
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:36,271
He's just too embarrassed
to suddenly change his tune.

62
00:03:37,301 --> 00:03:40,341
Hey, did you give Jeong Han
the punishment list?

63
00:03:40,841 --> 00:03:41,841
Of course, I did.

64
00:03:42,511 --> 00:03:45,181
It totally worked. Don't you worry.

65
00:03:45,681 --> 00:03:46,681
Good.

66
00:03:47,151 --> 00:03:48,151
You trust me, right?

67
00:03:58,291 --> 00:03:59,291
Right now, I...

68
00:03:59,691 --> 00:04:02,701
It feels like all those good moments
we had are tainted,

69
00:04:03,801 --> 00:04:04,931
and it's tearing me apart.

70
00:04:05,571 --> 00:04:08,571
That's why you should forgive them.
Because you're the one in pain.

71
00:04:09,801 --> 00:04:11,901
Mom once told me...

72
00:04:12,641 --> 00:04:15,411
that forgiveness is about
setting yourself free.

73
00:04:16,141 --> 00:04:19,611
It's a choice you make for yourself,
to let go of your anger.

74
00:04:28,621 --> 00:04:30,461
"The punishment list is..."

75
00:04:30,721 --> 00:04:32,891
"a self-imposed
disciplinary pledge..."

76
00:04:33,461 --> 00:04:34,991
"Yang Dong Ik wrote..."

77
00:04:35,501 --> 00:04:40,501
"to acknowledge his past mistakes
and help restore his friendship."

78
00:04:51,511 --> 00:04:52,751
This is driving me nuts.

79
00:04:53,281 --> 00:04:55,581
What the heck is
Gong Jeong Han thinking?

80
00:04:59,251 --> 00:05:00,351
Hey, Se Ri.

81
00:05:00,651 --> 00:05:03,361
Honey, did Dr. Gong show up
for the joint consultation?

82
00:05:04,061 --> 00:05:05,321
Yes, he came and left.

83
00:05:06,061 --> 00:05:08,431
That's a relief. I guess
he's starting to come around, right?

84
00:05:08,801 --> 00:05:10,461
That's what I thought, but...

85
00:05:11,231 --> 00:05:12,601
Get this, that jerk...

86
00:05:13,031 --> 00:05:14,901
He's going to meet
Councilor Hwang alone.

87
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:16,871
Alone? But why?

88
00:05:17,241 --> 00:05:18,401
How should I know?

89
00:05:18,671 --> 00:05:21,511
You don't think he'd rat us out
to Councilor Hwang...

90
00:05:21,841 --> 00:05:24,111
for uploading that video, do you?

91
00:05:24,811 --> 00:05:27,251
Jeong Han isn't trying
to get back at me, is he?

92
00:05:28,881 --> 00:05:31,521
Of course not.
He came in for the consultation,

93
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:33,521
and he agreed to be
on "Human Theater."

94
00:05:33,891 --> 00:05:37,091
We have the pre-interview tomorrow,
plus Dong Suk's grand opening.

95
00:05:37,191 --> 00:05:41,261
He's probably making peace slowly.
Don't be so anxious, okay?

96
00:05:41,391 --> 00:05:43,401
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

97
00:05:43,461 --> 00:05:44,461
All right.

98
00:05:45,131 --> 00:05:47,071
By the way, why did you call?

99
00:05:48,001 --> 00:05:49,871
Right.
I forgot I was the one who called.

100
00:05:50,401 --> 00:05:51,671
Honey...

101
00:05:52,271 --> 00:05:55,241
Could you give Hyun Bin a call?

102
00:05:55,711 --> 00:05:57,941
Hyun Bin? Me?

103
00:05:58,781 --> 00:06:02,951
You should call and ask him to come
to the grand opening tomorrow.

104
00:06:03,821 --> 00:06:05,921
Are you that uncomfortable
about what happened...

105
00:06:06,591 --> 00:06:08,421
that you can't even call
Hyun Bin yourself?

106
00:06:09,291 --> 00:06:11,821
It's not exactly that.

107
00:06:11,821 --> 00:06:13,331
Since things are awkward
between you and him too,

108
00:06:13,391 --> 00:06:14,991
I figured you should
at least hear his voice.

109
00:06:16,601 --> 00:06:17,601
Fine.

110
00:06:19,871 --> 00:06:20,971
This is so frustrating.

111
00:06:21,571 --> 00:06:24,501
If Hyun Bin isn't marrying the VP,
then who on earth is it?

112
00:06:26,711 --> 00:06:27,711
Gong Ju Ah.

113
00:06:28,711 --> 00:06:29,711
Yes.

114
00:06:30,211 --> 00:06:31,911
Gong Ju Ah must know who it is.

115
00:06:33,281 --> 00:06:36,881
At the grand opening tomorrow,
I'll ask her behind Hyun Bin's back.

116
00:06:38,621 --> 00:06:40,151
(Taehan)

117
00:06:40,221 --> 00:06:42,721
You're revamping
the FG online store?

118
00:06:43,021 --> 00:06:44,021
Yes.

119
00:06:44,361 --> 00:06:47,191
The longer people stay on the site,
the more likely they are to buy.

120
00:06:50,431 --> 00:06:51,501
Okay.

121
00:06:52,671 --> 00:06:54,431
At the next board meeting,

122
00:06:54,431 --> 00:06:56,441
I'll propose switching your contract
to long-term.

123
00:06:57,401 --> 00:07:00,241
You're just thrilled to tie me down,
aren't you?

124
00:07:00,411 --> 00:07:01,511
Totally.

125
00:07:02,941 --> 00:07:03,981
But...

126
00:07:04,441 --> 00:07:06,381
why are your families
on bad terms again?

127
00:07:06,851 --> 00:07:09,081
I thought things got better
after your stepmom...

128
00:07:09,081 --> 00:07:11,251
helped Ms. Gong
at the disciplinary hearing.

129
00:07:12,251 --> 00:07:13,891
She wasn't helping her.

130
00:07:14,451 --> 00:07:15,891
She was just cleaning up
her own mess.

131
00:07:16,191 --> 00:07:17,891
What? What do you mean?

132
00:07:18,621 --> 00:07:19,761
That video...

133
00:07:20,331 --> 00:07:22,061
My parents were the ones
who posted it.

134
00:07:25,901 --> 00:07:27,131
Hey, seriously?

135
00:07:27,601 --> 00:07:31,171
She uploaded that video of herself
rolling down the hill?

136
00:07:31,741 --> 00:07:32,741
Yes.

137
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:37,281
Wow, his stepmom is something else.

138
00:07:37,611 --> 00:07:38,611
Tell me about it.

139
00:07:39,111 --> 00:07:40,381
So, wait.

140
00:07:41,111 --> 00:07:45,421
She almost got you fired,
and then played the savior?

141
00:07:46,851 --> 00:07:48,321
That's some next-level scheming.

142
00:07:51,561 --> 00:07:56,101
Gosh, are you sure you'll be okay?
She's one intense mother-in-law.

143
00:07:57,161 --> 00:08:00,731
But what can I do?
I like Director Yang so much.

144
00:08:03,171 --> 00:08:06,241
Man, Director Yang must be having
a really hard time with this.

145
00:08:11,941 --> 00:08:13,511
Still, I'm actually...

146
00:08:14,511 --> 00:08:15,951
kind of grateful to your stepmom.

147
00:08:16,421 --> 00:08:19,651
Why? Because the video
helped us go viral?

148
00:08:20,191 --> 00:08:21,751
Well, there's that.

149
00:08:22,991 --> 00:08:24,761
Your stepmom seems like
one of those people.

150
00:08:25,121 --> 00:08:26,131
You mean?

151
00:08:26,231 --> 00:08:28,061
Terrifying
if they're on the other side,

152
00:08:28,491 --> 00:08:30,401
but a rock if they're on your side.
You know?

153
00:08:31,601 --> 00:08:33,631
Honestly, I felt this
when we were studying abroad too,

154
00:08:33,631 --> 00:08:35,271
but she's a remarkable woman.

155
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:37,801
She'll go through anything
for her family.

156
00:08:39,111 --> 00:08:41,871
- I wish I could be like that.
- By all means.

157
00:08:42,111 --> 00:08:44,641
(Taehan Group)

158
00:08:47,881 --> 00:08:48,881
Yes, Dad.

159
00:08:49,021 --> 00:08:53,351
Your stepmother's been good to you.
Yet she has to walk on eggshells.

160
00:08:53,421 --> 00:08:54,621
How can you make her so afraid
to even call?

161
00:08:55,191 --> 00:08:56,761
My stepmother's walking on eggshells
around me?

162
00:08:57,621 --> 00:08:59,091
Your aunt's store is having
its grand opening tomorrow.

163
00:08:59,391 --> 00:09:01,491
Come and properly apologize. Got it?

164
00:09:06,071 --> 00:09:09,371
Ju Ah's family is letting it slide,
but he's back to yelling at me.

165
00:09:09,501 --> 00:09:10,501
Unbelievable.

166
00:09:11,001 --> 00:09:13,511
So for them, Dr. Han Seong Mi is
the only one in the dark, right?

167
00:09:13,871 --> 00:09:17,711
Yes. If Dr. Han had found out,
she wouldn't have just let it go.

168
00:09:18,481 --> 00:09:22,011
- That would've been interesting.
- Yes, a real riot.

169
00:09:23,151 --> 00:09:24,151
By any chance,

170
00:09:24,851 --> 00:09:26,791
about me hiding my relationship
with Ms. Gong...

171
00:09:27,121 --> 00:09:28,191
Were you really upset?

172
00:09:29,361 --> 00:09:32,961
Well, I was, but I'm over it now.

173
00:09:33,491 --> 00:09:35,391
Because I've got a new guy friend.

174
00:09:36,201 --> 00:09:37,201
What?

175
00:09:38,561 --> 00:09:39,571
A guy friend?

176
00:09:39,901 --> 00:09:42,171
You're the Vice President's
new guy friend?

177
00:09:43,071 --> 00:09:46,311
- What? Are you jealous?
- No, I just can't believe it.

178
00:09:47,111 --> 00:09:48,941
Why not? What's wrong with me?

179
00:09:48,941 --> 00:09:51,741
You know, she jumped at the offer.

180
00:09:51,981 --> 00:09:53,681
That's a relief.

181
00:09:53,781 --> 00:09:56,321
Actually, it seemed
the VP and Director Yang...

182
00:09:56,321 --> 00:09:57,781
were growing distant because of me,

183
00:09:58,021 --> 00:09:59,421
and I was getting a little worried.

184
00:09:59,491 --> 00:10:02,521
Don't worry about them. Hurry up
and get your fathers to make up,

185
00:10:02,591 --> 00:10:05,321
and clear this all up, will you?
This fake boyfriend role is just...

186
00:10:05,391 --> 00:10:08,391
super uncomfortable and creepy.
It's also a great insult...

187
00:10:08,461 --> 00:10:09,661
to my future girlfriend!

188
00:10:10,831 --> 00:10:14,071
Hey, I'm trying my best, you know.
Since you met my family,

189
00:10:14,131 --> 00:10:16,071
Director Yang has been
in a terrible mood.

190
00:10:16,771 --> 00:10:19,941
Of course, he is.
Imagine how jealous he must be.

191
00:10:20,171 --> 00:10:24,181
Hey, stop provoking Director Yang.
You're going to get punched.

192
00:10:24,911 --> 00:10:25,981
He wouldn't dare.

193
00:10:26,381 --> 00:10:29,011
Because I've got the VP
in my corner.

194
00:10:29,421 --> 00:10:31,651
For crying out loud.
I can't with you...

195
00:10:32,891 --> 00:10:34,251
This all looks good, but...

196
00:10:34,721 --> 00:10:36,591
doesn't this one feel a bit jarring?

197
00:10:37,161 --> 00:10:39,191
Should we ask them
to desaturate it a bit?

198
00:10:39,531 --> 00:10:40,561
Well...

199
00:10:43,401 --> 00:10:47,101
No flirting on company time.
Have you forgotten where you are?

200
00:10:47,171 --> 00:10:49,271
It's not what it looks like.

201
00:10:50,341 --> 00:10:54,571
We saw Mr. Park and Ms. Gong nearby
on Sunday.

202
00:10:54,771 --> 00:10:58,341
- And?
- They had a bouquet and a gift box.

203
00:10:58,481 --> 00:11:02,181
- And what's your point?
- They wore matching outfits.

204
00:11:03,821 --> 00:11:04,921
- Matching outfits?
- Matching outfits?

205
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:06,591
Yes.

206
00:11:06,891 --> 00:11:09,391
It looked exactly like
they were going to meet the parents.

207
00:11:09,461 --> 00:11:12,361
No way.
Those two are just best friends.

208
00:11:12,421 --> 00:11:15,331
Well, sometimes best friends
end up dating, right?

209
00:11:15,461 --> 00:11:17,001
That's how it was with us.

210
00:11:19,671 --> 00:11:21,731
- What?
- I think I got something in my eye.

211
00:11:21,731 --> 00:11:23,771
- Want me to blow it out for you?
- Yes, do it.

212
00:11:32,881 --> 00:11:34,581
Hey, open your eyes.
Open up. Come on.

213
00:11:35,051 --> 00:11:36,321
Hey, what are you doing?

214
00:11:36,421 --> 00:11:39,291
How else can I get it out?
Come on, open it. I'll get it out.

215
00:11:39,351 --> 00:11:40,821
- Don't. It's gross.
- Come on.

216
00:11:40,891 --> 00:11:42,121
- Why? What's the big deal?
- Hey.

217
00:11:47,491 --> 00:11:49,431
You see, I...

218
00:11:49,931 --> 00:11:52,031
I think I saw Dr. Gong.

219
00:11:52,631 --> 00:11:54,701
- My eldest son?
- No.

220
00:11:55,301 --> 00:11:56,771
Your husband.

221
00:11:57,241 --> 00:12:00,571
Dr. Gong,
the one who left home 30 years ago.

222
00:12:12,451 --> 00:12:14,721
Where did she say she saw Gi Cheol?

223
00:12:15,221 --> 00:12:19,861
At a place in Seongdam.
She said it was an optician's shop.

224
00:12:22,331 --> 00:12:23,361
What about In Ok?

225
00:12:24,131 --> 00:12:26,201
Did she say anything about my wife?

226
00:12:28,671 --> 00:12:32,201
No. I was so flustered...

227
00:12:32,641 --> 00:12:34,641
that I didn't think to ask.

228
00:12:37,611 --> 00:12:39,111
What should we do?

229
00:12:51,561 --> 00:12:54,031
Boss, the grand opening rice cakes
are here.

230
00:12:54,091 --> 00:12:56,801
- Good, they're here already.
- Oh, they look delicious.

231
00:12:56,861 --> 00:12:58,731
- Hey, stop that!
- That hurts!

232
00:12:58,801 --> 00:13:01,171
Hey! What is that on your nails?

233
00:13:01,271 --> 00:13:05,041
What? I did my nails
to look pretty for Woo Jae.

234
00:13:05,641 --> 00:13:09,011
Woo Jae, what do you think? Pretty?
I did them myself.

235
00:13:09,811 --> 00:13:13,051
Eun Bin. This is a restaurant.
You should keep your nails short.

236
00:13:13,711 --> 00:13:17,051
And tie your hair up.
Why is it all over the place?

237
00:13:17,351 --> 00:13:20,791
Yes, you should tie it back neatly
like Min Seo does.

238
00:13:21,691 --> 00:13:23,461
Can you not compare me to her?

239
00:13:25,361 --> 00:13:27,331
Oh, looks like more flowers arrived.

240
00:13:32,531 --> 00:13:35,871
"To my beloved Endorphin."

241
00:13:36,271 --> 00:13:37,641
"To Suk?"

242
00:13:37,701 --> 00:13:39,641
(To my beloved Endorphin, Suk)

243
00:13:40,741 --> 00:13:43,411
What? And you're telling me
you don't have a boyfriend?

244
00:13:44,881 --> 00:13:46,911
Hey, it's just a friend
messing with me.

245
00:13:47,351 --> 00:13:50,651
A friend?
What kind of "friend" sends this?

246
00:13:50,751 --> 00:13:51,751
Right?

247
00:13:52,451 --> 00:13:55,691
Eun Bin, does your aunt
have a boyfriend?

248
00:13:55,751 --> 00:13:58,161
Yes. I think it's someone
from Onjeong.

249
00:13:58,761 --> 00:14:03,231
- Oh, really?
- Yes, I heard they went to a motel.

250
00:14:03,331 --> 00:14:04,531
What? A motel?

251
00:14:05,101 --> 00:14:08,071
Why are you so shocked?
They're adults. What's the big deal?

252
00:14:08,231 --> 00:14:11,301
I'll find out who this guy is.
You just wait...

253
00:14:12,341 --> 00:14:13,341
Gosh, Auntie!

254
00:14:17,581 --> 00:14:19,811
Eun Bin, you take the rice cakes
to the market's A-wing first.

255
00:14:19,881 --> 00:14:22,311
If you run out, come back for more.
Woo Jae...

256
00:14:22,381 --> 00:14:25,151
Why do we have to go separately?
I want to go with Woo Jae.

257
00:14:25,221 --> 00:14:26,521
So it can feel like a date.

258
00:14:27,221 --> 00:14:29,691
Hand them out and return to prep.
What are you talking about?

259
00:14:29,761 --> 00:14:33,891
No way. I want to go with Woo Jae.
That's why I took this job.

260
00:14:33,961 --> 00:14:36,831
If you keep this up,
I'm telling your mom.

261
00:14:36,961 --> 00:14:37,961
That's a low blow!

262
00:14:38,661 --> 00:14:41,131
- Just hurry up and go.
- Thanks.

263
00:14:42,171 --> 00:14:44,471
- Gosh, this is heavy.
- Hurry back.

264
00:14:44,501 --> 00:14:45,671
Gosh, seriously...

265
00:14:46,071 --> 00:14:49,271
- So I'll take the B-wing, right?
- Yes, take the small box for that.

266
00:14:49,581 --> 00:14:51,881
And take this one
to your dad's clinic.

267
00:14:52,181 --> 00:14:53,851
All of this? It's way too much.

268
00:14:53,951 --> 00:14:56,721
Not at all!
There are tons of people.

269
00:14:56,921 --> 00:14:58,581
And also, your uncle...

270
00:14:58,651 --> 00:15:00,551
has always loved these rice cakes.

271
00:15:00,991 --> 00:15:02,251
I see...

272
00:15:04,121 --> 00:15:06,991
- You knew that?
- Yes. What?

273
00:15:08,431 --> 00:15:09,431
Oh, of course.

274
00:15:09,761 --> 00:15:12,731
Hey, do you have any idea
how long we've known each other?

275
00:15:17,241 --> 00:15:18,241
That's a relief.

276
00:15:18,471 --> 00:15:20,441
So Uncle's crush isn't one-sided
after all.

277
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:23,581
Gosh, but still, I'm really worried.

278
00:15:35,151 --> 00:15:36,891
Here, open wide.

279
00:15:39,461 --> 00:15:40,461
Oh, stop.

280
00:15:43,161 --> 00:15:47,471
Oh, man.
The doctors will make up, right?

281
00:15:48,571 --> 00:15:49,571
Well...

282
00:15:50,341 --> 00:15:52,241
Even if they do make up,

283
00:15:52,841 --> 00:15:54,711
don't you think it will be difficult
for you two?

284
00:15:55,771 --> 00:15:57,381
"You two?"
Who are you talking about?

285
00:15:57,911 --> 00:16:01,481
The two of you who fed each other
popcorn at the movies yesterday.

286
00:16:01,651 --> 00:16:04,821
- What?
- I saw you two at the movies.

287
00:16:05,881 --> 00:16:07,321
Hey, you... Hush.

288
00:16:08,791 --> 00:16:10,521
Don't tell anyone about this.
Got it?

289
00:16:10,891 --> 00:16:13,561
I don't know.
Even if I don't say anything...

290
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:15,331
Looks like word's getting out soon.

291
00:16:15,531 --> 00:16:16,601
Why?

292
00:16:16,731 --> 00:16:19,201
You wear your heart on your sleeve.

293
00:16:20,201 --> 00:16:24,141
If it's obvious, give me a sign.
I absolutely can't let anyone know.

294
00:16:24,341 --> 00:16:25,341
All right.

295
00:16:25,601 --> 00:16:27,841
- Come on, eat.
- Darn it...

296
00:16:28,311 --> 00:16:29,311
Eat up.

297
00:16:30,411 --> 00:16:34,511
- Uncle. Nurse Oh.
- Hey! What're you doing here?

298
00:16:34,681 --> 00:16:36,481
I brought rice cakes
for our opening.

299
00:16:36,481 --> 00:16:37,821
And Uncle, these are for you.

300
00:16:39,051 --> 00:16:40,791
Wow, you brought a ton.

301
00:16:41,221 --> 00:16:43,561
What kind of rice cakes are these?

302
00:16:44,691 --> 00:16:48,761
Wow! This is...
This is my favorite rice cake.

303
00:16:49,801 --> 00:16:52,201
Of course.
She knows exactly what I like.

304
00:16:52,701 --> 00:16:56,101
- Just as I thought.
- Oh, you're Dr. Gong's son.

305
00:16:56,171 --> 00:16:57,171
Hello, ma'am.

306
00:16:57,641 --> 00:17:00,641
- I brought these for our opening.
- Grand opening for what?

307
00:17:00,841 --> 00:17:04,011
I'm working at the barbecue place
in front of the community hall now.

308
00:17:04,141 --> 00:17:05,141
That place?

309
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:09,081
I thought I heard
Dr. Yang's sister took over.

310
00:17:09,151 --> 00:17:11,151
Yes, the restaurant reopened today.

311
00:17:11,221 --> 00:17:12,851
Please stop by sometime
when you have a chance.

312
00:17:12,921 --> 00:17:16,021
- Okay. I'll be sure to stop by.
- Great.

313
00:17:18,061 --> 00:17:20,131
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

314
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:23,031
You should bring your aerobics group
for one of your get-togethers.

315
00:17:23,101 --> 00:17:25,701
The restaurant is really spacious,
so it's perfect for big groups.

316
00:17:25,861 --> 00:17:28,231
And don't even get me started
on how good the meat is.

317
00:17:28,871 --> 00:17:31,971
But running a business is no joke.
I wonder if she can handle it.

318
00:17:32,201 --> 00:17:34,441
Why do you say that?
She managed the clinic...

319
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:37,511
for years. All that experience
has to count for something, right?

320
00:17:37,611 --> 00:17:39,881
She's so easygoing and cheerful.

321
00:17:39,881 --> 00:17:42,351
She's great with customers, too!

322
00:17:43,281 --> 00:17:44,281
All right.

323
00:17:44,581 --> 00:17:46,621
- Be sure to stop by.
- Okay.

324
00:17:50,161 --> 00:17:53,491
Hello. The barbecue spot by the hall
just opened.

325
00:17:53,561 --> 00:17:55,761
Please stop by. Thank you.

326
00:17:58,861 --> 00:18:01,971
Hello! The barbecue spot by the hall
just opened.

327
00:18:02,371 --> 00:18:04,571
- You should check it out.
- Okay, we will.

328
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:06,741
- Yes, hello.
- Real subtle.

329
00:18:06,811 --> 00:18:09,641
The barbecue spot by the hall
just opened. Please check it out.

330
00:18:09,841 --> 00:18:11,611
- Thank you.
- Hello.

331
00:18:11,741 --> 00:18:15,351
Are you here for lunch? I was about
to head over to the substation.

332
00:18:15,681 --> 00:18:18,581
- My gosh.
- Here. We just reopened.

333
00:18:18,851 --> 00:18:21,151
Thank you so much.
I'll definitely stop by.

334
00:18:21,221 --> 00:18:22,691
- Please do.
- Will do.

335
00:18:29,901 --> 00:18:30,901
Hello.

336
00:18:32,001 --> 00:18:34,071
- Ma'am, one order of noodles.
- Sure.

337
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:37,241
Hey, Officer Jung.
Come over here. Join us. Come on.

338
00:18:39,871 --> 00:18:40,871
Eat up.

339
00:18:59,691 --> 00:19:02,331
Let's go with this
for the main shot.

340
00:19:03,031 --> 00:19:06,601
Man, it was hard picking a solo shot
for Dr. Han.

341
00:19:06,671 --> 00:19:07,931
Every single one is a keeper.

342
00:19:09,601 --> 00:19:13,741
What if we post the B-cuts...

343
00:19:13,811 --> 00:19:14,811
on our social media channels later?

344
00:19:16,011 --> 00:19:18,081
I love that. That's a great idea.

345
00:19:19,481 --> 00:19:24,081
Let's pre-release the main cuts
before the show to build hype...

346
00:19:24,221 --> 00:19:26,421
and post the B-cuts on social media.

347
00:19:27,151 --> 00:19:28,921
That's a wrap for today.

348
00:19:29,891 --> 00:19:32,161
Gosh, I can't stand it.
I'm dying of curiosity.

349
00:19:32,721 --> 00:19:33,891
I just have to ask.

350
00:19:34,261 --> 00:19:37,031
- Ask what?
- Ms. Gong. And Mr. Park.

351
00:19:38,101 --> 00:19:39,261
What were you two doing on Sunday?

352
00:19:44,501 --> 00:19:46,511
Mr. Park, you two were wearing
matching outfits.

353
00:19:46,871 --> 00:19:48,771
Did you meet Ms. Gong's parents?

354
00:19:49,341 --> 00:19:52,081
What are you talking about?
That's ridiculous. My goodness.

355
00:19:53,681 --> 00:19:56,851
Matching outfits? Come on.
Our clothes were just similar.

356
00:19:57,151 --> 00:19:58,321
You two are dating, aren't you?

357
00:19:58,851 --> 00:20:00,251
You went to meet the family, right?

358
00:20:01,451 --> 00:20:04,721
Gosh, don't be ridiculous.
She's not my type.

359
00:20:05,361 --> 00:20:09,461
Gosh, please. No way I'd date her.
That's disgusting.

360
00:20:10,531 --> 00:20:12,901
Do you have to be so dramatic
about it?

361
00:20:14,331 --> 00:20:16,231
Mr. Park? A word.

362
00:20:16,801 --> 00:20:18,401
Oh, sure.

363
00:20:24,981 --> 00:20:27,781
Ms. Gong, are you sure
it's not true?

364
00:20:27,881 --> 00:20:30,221
Didn't you hear him?
He literally said "disgusting."

365
00:20:30,681 --> 00:20:32,821
You know what they say.
The lady doth protest too much.

366
00:20:34,991 --> 00:20:38,161
I said no! Just drop it, will you?
Gosh, seriously.

367
00:20:44,801 --> 00:20:46,871
So, you're the VP's "guy friend,"
are you?

368
00:20:48,571 --> 00:20:50,771
- Yes, sir.
- And who gave you permission?

369
00:20:51,571 --> 00:20:54,611
- Do I need to get your permission?
- Of course, you do.

370
00:20:55,471 --> 00:20:56,641
So, you'll give me
your permission, right?

371
00:20:59,141 --> 00:21:01,011
- You pass.
- Thanks.

372
00:21:02,181 --> 00:21:04,481
So anyway, why did you ask me
to meet you here?

373
00:21:05,281 --> 00:21:09,351
I need help picking out a ring.
You know Ms. Gong's taste best.

374
00:21:10,621 --> 00:21:12,391
Well, you're not wrong there.

375
00:21:13,661 --> 00:21:14,931
So, what's the ring for?

376
00:21:15,891 --> 00:21:17,031
Are you planning on proposing?

377
00:21:17,831 --> 00:21:21,431
I wish. I'm just buying it
because I'm feeling a little down.

378
00:21:21,901 --> 00:21:24,801
I think getting a ring will at least
make me feel less anxious.

379
00:21:27,871 --> 00:21:29,811
I'm sorry
I'm the one who met her family...

380
00:21:29,811 --> 00:21:30,841
and made a good impression.

381
00:21:32,181 --> 00:21:34,511
What can I do?
The situation is what it is.

382
00:21:35,351 --> 00:21:38,051
But you know,
both at home and at work,

383
00:21:38,321 --> 00:21:41,151
it's so hard hiding my feelings
like this.

384
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:45,091
The day will come
when you can proudly go public.

385
00:21:46,531 --> 00:21:47,761
I hope so.

386
00:21:48,391 --> 00:21:50,031
What about this one?

387
00:21:50,301 --> 00:21:53,031
This one is flashy and pretty.
It would look great on my princess.

388
00:21:53,531 --> 00:21:56,771
No. You really don't know
her taste at all.

389
00:21:57,801 --> 00:21:59,641
Then what about this one? This.

390
00:22:01,941 --> 00:22:02,941
Oh, my.

391
00:22:05,641 --> 00:22:07,951
This one. Do you think
my princess will like it?

392
00:22:08,111 --> 00:22:11,721
No, that one's not it either.
I like this one.

393
00:22:16,721 --> 00:22:19,961
- What do you think?
- Wow, it's beautiful.

394
00:22:20,531 --> 00:22:22,191
Then should I get this one for her?

395
00:22:22,831 --> 00:22:23,831
Go for it.

396
00:22:28,831 --> 00:22:29,841
Hello.

397
00:22:30,201 --> 00:22:33,771
I called. I'm here about
the Onjeong branch acquisition.

398
00:22:33,971 --> 00:22:37,281
Yes. Hello.
You must be Ms. Cha Se Ri.

399
00:22:37,381 --> 00:22:39,041
- Please have a seat over here.
- Okay.

400
00:22:40,881 --> 00:22:43,151
Then I'll walk you through
the transfer process.

401
00:22:43,421 --> 00:22:44,421
Okay.

402
00:22:50,961 --> 00:22:52,591
(Jogak Photo Studio)

403
00:22:59,701 --> 00:23:01,871
Oh, here, let me get that.
I'll carry it for you.

404
00:23:03,601 --> 00:23:04,601
Thank you.

405
00:23:05,271 --> 00:23:07,971
So what brings you to the market?
Did you need to get something?

406
00:23:08,041 --> 00:23:12,341
I was just buying books for Ji Hu
and looking around.

407
00:23:12,481 --> 00:23:16,311
- I see. Just expense all of it.
- No, it's fine.

408
00:23:16,381 --> 00:23:18,581
- No, really. Just a second.
- Okay.

409
00:23:18,651 --> 00:23:20,521
Hi, there. Can I get some
of these wild greens, please?

410
00:23:20,591 --> 00:23:23,721
Welcome! It's the doctor's wife.
Making a side dish with them?

411
00:23:23,921 --> 00:23:27,431
- Yes, and soybean paste soup, too.
- I see.

412
00:23:28,461 --> 00:23:30,731
By the way, who's this with you?

413
00:23:31,061 --> 00:23:33,301
She's not your daughter, is she?
A niece, perhaps?

414
00:23:34,531 --> 00:23:35,571
No, I'm not.

415
00:23:35,871 --> 00:23:37,071
She's my daughter's friend.

416
00:23:37,301 --> 00:23:41,211
Oh, my! But it's amazing
how much you two look alike.

417
00:23:43,681 --> 00:23:44,811
I don't think so.

418
00:23:46,211 --> 00:23:48,011
- Enjoy!
- Thank you.

419
00:23:48,481 --> 00:23:50,151
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

420
00:23:50,221 --> 00:23:51,651
Hey, Jeong Han!

421
00:23:53,151 --> 00:23:57,761
- Hey. Off to see Councilor Hwang?
- What? Yes.

422
00:23:58,391 --> 00:23:59,461
What?

423
00:24:00,531 --> 00:24:02,131
Darn it...

424
00:24:06,001 --> 00:24:07,001
My gosh...

425
00:24:08,271 --> 00:24:09,271
Hey.

426
00:24:09,941 --> 00:24:13,041
I'll find out where he's going
and call you.

427
00:24:14,041 --> 00:24:15,041
You scared me.

428
00:24:15,571 --> 00:24:16,681
I'll call you!

429
00:24:27,221 --> 00:24:28,221
Honey.

430
00:24:28,651 --> 00:24:31,621
I'll make you lunch at home
until the store opens.

431
00:24:32,061 --> 00:24:33,861
Father got indigestion
from eating out a few times...

432
00:24:33,861 --> 00:24:35,461
and can't even eat dinner.

433
00:24:36,261 --> 00:24:37,331
Don't worry about it.

434
00:24:37,961 --> 00:24:40,171
I'll make lunch and eat with Dad.

435
00:24:40,871 --> 00:24:42,501
As if you know how to cook anything.

436
00:24:43,971 --> 00:24:44,971
Here.

437
00:24:48,971 --> 00:24:53,111
Why is Dr. Gong so insistent
on meeting Councilor Hwang alone?

438
00:24:53,381 --> 00:24:55,351
I have no idea what he's thinking.

439
00:24:55,881 --> 00:24:58,481
Dae Han said he'd look into it
and get back to me.

440
00:24:59,721 --> 00:25:01,791
- Who?
- Dr. Gong's younger brother.

441
00:25:02,191 --> 00:25:03,691
He's been trying to win me over
lately.

442
00:25:04,121 --> 00:25:05,521
You know, Manager Gong?

443
00:25:05,821 --> 00:25:07,491
Yes, I know who you mean.

444
00:25:07,761 --> 00:25:10,601
He's the guy whose ex-wife cheated
with Dong Suk's ex-husband.

445
00:25:12,201 --> 00:25:13,571
That's all in the past now.

446
00:25:14,271 --> 00:25:16,031
Dong Suk's moved on
and is doing fine.

447
00:25:16,531 --> 00:25:17,571
I heard
she even has a boyfriend now.

448
00:25:18,441 --> 00:25:21,971
It seems like she does,
but she won't tell us who he is.

449
00:25:22,971 --> 00:25:27,211
He's not a weirdo like Yong Gil,
is he?

450
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:29,651
Should I do some digging?
See what kind of guy he is?

451
00:25:30,921 --> 00:25:35,351
So? Wait.
Did it go well with Councilor Hwang?

452
00:25:35,721 --> 00:25:37,721
Hey, were you waiting for me?

453
00:25:38,091 --> 00:25:41,061
Yes, of course. I was worried
something might happen.

454
00:25:41,461 --> 00:25:44,661
But why did you go alone?
You should've gone with Dong Ik.

455
00:25:48,031 --> 00:25:51,641
Gosh, you guys agreed to team up,
so are you still holding a grudge?

456
00:25:52,601 --> 00:25:56,311
Come on, just tell me.
Why did you meet him alone?

457
00:25:56,441 --> 00:25:59,181
Hey, you're so persistent.
Seriously.

458
00:25:59,241 --> 00:26:02,881
Come on, tell me. What was it about?
Did you say something bad?

459
00:26:05,781 --> 00:26:08,091
Why did you ask to see me alone?

460
00:26:09,251 --> 00:26:12,961
Meeting with both of you
was my wife's idea.

461
00:26:13,531 --> 00:26:16,801
Frankly,
I'm not a big fan of Yang Dong Ik.

462
00:26:17,231 --> 00:26:19,431
And it sounds like
his wife is pretty unlikeable, too.

463
00:26:20,101 --> 00:26:21,831
I see.

464
00:26:22,301 --> 00:26:23,301
Dr. Gong.

465
00:26:23,571 --> 00:26:26,371
Do you have to be on that show
with him?

466
00:26:27,041 --> 00:26:30,481
If it were just your family,
I'd be happy to join you.

467
00:26:33,281 --> 00:26:34,281
Councilor Hwang.

468
00:26:35,611 --> 00:26:37,051
My friend, Dong Ik...

469
00:26:37,981 --> 00:26:39,221
Once he sets his mind on a goal,

470
00:26:39,881 --> 00:26:43,251
he has the guts to endure
any kind of humiliation.

471
00:26:43,621 --> 00:26:46,461
One, two, three, four!

472
00:26:46,461 --> 00:26:49,091
- Once he gets focused on something,
- Like this! Our Onjeong Market...

473
00:26:49,161 --> 00:26:51,001
he tends to dive in headfirst
with real passion.

474
00:26:51,061 --> 00:26:52,561
Sales will increase fivefold!

475
00:26:52,561 --> 00:26:55,001
I, Yang Dong Ik
will solve everything for you.

476
00:26:55,131 --> 00:26:56,501
He's so pure-hearted...

477
00:26:56,731 --> 00:26:57,741
- Oh, sure thing.
- that even a single compliment...

478
00:26:57,771 --> 00:26:59,141
makes him want to do anything
for you.

479
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:00,211
The nearby areas.

480
00:27:00,271 --> 00:27:05,041
And he's loyal enough
to risk his life for a friend.

481
00:27:06,141 --> 00:27:09,851
He handles civil complaints
and keeps the areas clean.

482
00:27:10,151 --> 00:27:11,851
He's the go-to problem-solver
at Onjeong Market,

483
00:27:12,181 --> 00:27:15,851
and he's working tirelessly
for the development of the market.

484
00:27:18,421 --> 00:27:20,191
If Dong Ik becomes
a city councilman,

485
00:27:21,031 --> 00:27:23,391
he will be a true public servant
with his boots on the ground.

486
00:27:25,261 --> 00:27:27,101
Because he has more scars
than anyone,

487
00:27:27,731 --> 00:27:30,201
he'll be able to empathize
with those who are struggling.

488
00:27:31,171 --> 00:27:35,111
And as much as he wants to be loved,
he knows how to love in return.

489
00:27:36,011 --> 00:27:39,011
That's the councilman he'll be, sir.

490
00:27:41,611 --> 00:27:43,381
Oh, man!

491
00:27:43,781 --> 00:27:47,521
Hey! You did great! You really did!

492
00:27:47,591 --> 00:27:49,521
Wow, your dazzling friendship
is bringing tears to my eyes.

493
00:27:49,521 --> 00:27:51,561
Hey, stop being so dramatic.

494
00:27:51,621 --> 00:27:54,361
Sorry. But what made you
have such a change of heart?

495
00:27:55,191 --> 00:27:59,261
After thinking it over, I could see
where he was coming from.

496
00:27:59,501 --> 00:28:03,401
Plus, I did promise
I'd grant him one wish.

497
00:28:03,901 --> 00:28:04,901
A wish?

498
00:28:05,571 --> 00:28:07,611
You did save my life once, you know.

499
00:28:07,711 --> 00:28:10,581
I'm going to grant you one wish.

500
00:28:11,181 --> 00:28:12,181
A wish?

501
00:28:12,741 --> 00:28:15,811
Of course.
My brother is a man of his word!

502
00:28:17,181 --> 00:28:19,521
It's all water under the bridge.

503
00:28:20,051 --> 00:28:22,451
I decided to stop being so petty
and move on.

504
00:28:24,461 --> 00:28:25,721
Yes, that's really great. But...

505
00:28:26,291 --> 00:28:29,991
Then you should tell Dong Ik
right away.

506
00:28:30,061 --> 00:28:31,701
He thinks it's the end of the world
right now.

507
00:28:32,101 --> 00:28:35,301
At this hour?
We'll see him soon enough anyway.

508
00:28:36,271 --> 00:28:37,501
Oh, I guess so.

509
00:28:37,841 --> 00:28:41,571
Yes, I'll tell him.
Now, as for you...

510
00:28:42,371 --> 00:28:44,541
Stop playing spy, you little punk!

511
00:28:46,381 --> 00:28:48,711
Hey, how did you know I was the spy?

512
00:28:49,011 --> 00:28:52,551
Are you serious? How could I not?
That punishment list!

513
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:54,321
You could've at least had
someone else write it.

514
00:28:54,621 --> 00:28:56,091
Your handwriting
was a dead giveaway.

515
00:28:56,451 --> 00:28:59,521
Oh, man. Busted.

516
00:29:00,861 --> 00:29:03,161
Seriously, why did you go
to all that trouble for him?

517
00:29:04,261 --> 00:29:05,861
It's just... You guys...

518
00:29:06,531 --> 00:29:08,871
You all worked so hard
to mend your friendship,

519
00:29:09,401 --> 00:29:11,101
and it looked like it was about to
fall apart in an instant.

520
00:29:11,401 --> 00:29:12,671
I was just so upset.

521
00:29:13,571 --> 00:29:14,741
Gosh, you knucklehead.

522
00:29:15,711 --> 00:29:16,711
Get some rest.

523
00:29:18,411 --> 00:29:19,411
Hey!

524
00:29:19,881 --> 00:29:22,981
Hey, when you meet Dong Ik
and make up tomorrow,

525
00:29:23,181 --> 00:29:26,851
make sure you say something like,
"It's all thanks to Dae Han," okay?

526
00:29:27,351 --> 00:29:29,451
- Please, okay?
- Give me a break.

527
00:29:30,051 --> 00:29:33,761
- Thank you!
- That spy's my brother. Good grief.

528
00:29:45,671 --> 00:29:46,671
How strange.

529
00:29:47,311 --> 00:29:48,311
Something feels off.

530
00:29:49,471 --> 00:29:50,811
Why haven't I heard from him yet?

531
00:29:56,311 --> 00:29:57,321
He's not picking up?

532
00:29:58,651 --> 00:30:00,921
- Unbelievable.
- The call cannot be connected.

533
00:30:00,991 --> 00:30:01,991
He's not picking up.

534
00:30:02,821 --> 00:30:03,821
Don't tell me...

535
00:30:04,221 --> 00:30:06,461
Has that punk Gong Dae Han
turned on me, too?

536
00:30:09,591 --> 00:30:11,461
(Yang Dong Ik)

537
00:30:12,661 --> 00:30:15,371
Man, he must be sweating bullets
right now.

538
00:30:16,031 --> 00:30:17,041
Seriously.

539
00:30:18,371 --> 00:30:20,411
Uncle, what are you laughing about
over here?

540
00:30:20,471 --> 00:30:24,411
Oh, Ju Ah. Hey, have a seat.
Come here, I've got good news.

541
00:30:24,641 --> 00:30:25,641
Why? What is it?

542
00:30:25,911 --> 00:30:26,911
So...

543
00:30:27,551 --> 00:30:30,151
Your dad said
he's going to forgive Dong Ik.

544
00:30:31,121 --> 00:30:35,551
- Really?
- Yes. They're making up tomorrow.

545
00:30:35,751 --> 00:30:38,061
Oh, that's such a relief.

546
00:30:39,091 --> 00:30:43,961
See? Our little tag-team effort
totally worked.

547
00:30:45,531 --> 00:30:48,231
Wait, but Uncle,
why are you so happy about this?

548
00:30:48,331 --> 00:30:52,771
What? It's just...
Hey, a win is a win, right?

549
00:30:52,841 --> 00:30:56,241
- Yes, I guess so.
- Okay, I'm heading down.

550
00:30:56,371 --> 00:30:58,041
- Okay.
- Oh, wait.

551
00:30:58,811 --> 00:31:00,751
Oh, man.
He must've been pooping his pants.

552
00:31:01,581 --> 00:31:03,981
- Hey, I'm heading down.
- Okay.

553
00:31:04,851 --> 00:31:05,851
What was that about?

554
00:31:12,461 --> 00:31:14,761
I should go tell my endorphin.

555
00:31:15,591 --> 00:31:16,731
Oh, no.

556
00:31:17,361 --> 00:31:18,801
I'll tell her
when I see her tomorrow.

557
00:31:24,101 --> 00:31:26,201
- Did you enjoy your meal?
- Yes, it was delicious.

558
00:31:26,271 --> 00:31:28,211
- Thank you. Come again.
- We will.

559
00:31:32,611 --> 00:31:33,711
My endorphin.

560
00:31:34,051 --> 00:31:36,311
I have good news.
I'll tell you tomorrow.

561
00:31:36,781 --> 00:31:38,581
What a tease.

562
00:31:41,221 --> 00:31:43,721
Gosh, who is he?
Why are you being so secretive?

563
00:31:43,891 --> 00:31:46,461
Get back to work.
Stop following me around.

564
00:31:48,191 --> 00:31:51,201
I wasn't following you.
I came to tell you something.

565
00:31:51,601 --> 00:31:52,601
Tell me what? What is it?

566
00:31:53,161 --> 00:31:56,701
The families are coming tomorrow.
My job here is a secret, remember?

567
00:31:56,901 --> 00:31:59,741
If Mom sees me with Woo Jae,
she'll flip out.

568
00:32:04,211 --> 00:32:07,351
I don't know if all this is going
to do you any good, though.

569
00:32:07,651 --> 00:32:10,451
Looks like Woo Jae is into Min Seo,
not you.

570
00:32:11,281 --> 00:32:12,281
I know.

571
00:32:12,821 --> 00:32:14,251
- You do?
- Yes.

572
00:32:14,251 --> 00:32:18,261
But it's fine. As they say,
"Out of sight, out of mind."

573
00:32:18,461 --> 00:32:21,091
I'm going to stay by his side
and win him over.

574
00:32:21,491 --> 00:32:23,431
I will not be denied.

575
00:32:25,461 --> 00:32:29,671
- I like your attitude. Go for it!
- I will!

576
00:32:31,541 --> 00:32:32,541
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

577
00:32:32,801 --> 00:32:35,041
- How is everything?
- It's delicious.

578
00:32:35,341 --> 00:32:36,971
He's great at grilling the meat,
isn't he?

579
00:32:37,581 --> 00:32:38,581
Go away.

580
00:32:41,551 --> 00:32:43,881
Stepmother,
why didn't you call me directly?

581
00:32:43,951 --> 00:32:45,321
Why did you have Dad do it?

582
00:32:46,051 --> 00:32:48,991
After you said
you were disappointed in me,

583
00:32:49,391 --> 00:32:51,321
how could I be the first one
to call?

584
00:32:52,591 --> 00:32:54,931
Did I upset you that much?

585
00:32:56,031 --> 00:32:58,761
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't.

586
00:32:59,401 --> 00:33:04,071
I was too emotional last time.
I'm sorry if I hurt your feelings.

587
00:33:04,571 --> 00:33:07,101
It's fine.
I wasn't exactly blameless either.

588
00:33:08,311 --> 00:33:10,841
I'll stop by Aunt's restaurant
after work tomorrow.

589
00:33:11,441 --> 00:33:13,851
Okay, sounds good.
See you tomorrow, son.

590
00:33:32,631 --> 00:33:34,871
- Father.
- Yes?

591
00:33:39,871 --> 00:33:41,171
Aren't you hungry?

592
00:33:41,611 --> 00:33:45,981
This is brown rice tea.
It'll help settle your stomach.

593
00:33:47,251 --> 00:33:48,311
When my stomach's upset,

594
00:33:49,011 --> 00:33:51,981
it's better to skip a meal.
Don't worry about me.

595
00:33:52,351 --> 00:33:56,091
How could I not worry?
Father, you're this family's rock.

596
00:33:58,361 --> 00:34:01,161
So, do you like the shop
you're taking over?

597
00:34:01,631 --> 00:34:06,101
Yes, it's well-maintained and ideal
for me to run on my own.

598
00:34:06,531 --> 00:34:09,901
You'll do great at whatever you do,
Se Ri.

599
00:34:11,201 --> 00:34:13,571
I don't trust a single soul
in this world,

600
00:34:14,741 --> 00:34:16,711
but I trust you.

601
00:34:18,541 --> 00:34:21,111
I'll strive to be a daughter-in-law
worthy of that trust.

602
00:34:21,951 --> 00:34:23,351
I'm always so grateful, Father.

603
00:34:33,491 --> 00:34:35,731
- Mother.
- You're home.

604
00:34:36,531 --> 00:34:37,701
Why are you still awake?

605
00:34:38,101 --> 00:34:41,631
I just... I have a lot on my mind.

606
00:34:42,171 --> 00:34:43,471
But why are you home so late?

607
00:34:44,241 --> 00:34:46,941
The BBQ restaurant opens tomorrow,
so I have to be in early.

608
00:34:47,201 --> 00:34:48,971
I was trying to get some work done
ahead of time.

609
00:34:49,041 --> 00:34:52,011
Goodness, but still.
It's almost midnight.

610
00:34:52,611 --> 00:34:56,781
- You can't keep pushing yourself.
- Come on, Mother.

611
00:34:57,321 --> 00:35:01,121
I'm a doctor.
I know how to care for myself.

612
00:35:01,751 --> 00:35:04,791
Don't worry. I take proper vitamins
and supplements.

613
00:35:05,361 --> 00:35:06,461
Even so,

614
00:35:07,021 --> 00:35:09,991
why don't you get an IV drip
at the clinic?

615
00:35:10,601 --> 00:35:11,601
Okay, I will.

616
00:35:12,761 --> 00:35:14,701
So, what did you mean when you said
you had a lot on your mind?

617
00:35:21,971 --> 00:35:24,941
Where?
Where did they say they saw him?

618
00:35:25,881 --> 00:35:26,881
In Seongdam.

619
00:35:27,551 --> 00:35:30,211
No way.
That's right around the corner.

620
00:35:31,651 --> 00:35:34,851
It's not for certain.
It was Ms. Yong Soon.

621
00:35:35,391 --> 00:35:37,421
She said she saw him while visiting
her daughter's house there.

622
00:35:38,691 --> 00:35:40,421
So are you going to go see
for yourself?

623
00:35:42,391 --> 00:35:43,391
I don't know.

624
00:35:45,161 --> 00:35:47,801
He's been so close by all this time
without showing his face...

625
00:35:48,401 --> 00:35:50,701
What's the point of
looking for him now?

626
00:35:51,571 --> 00:35:53,171
His story is predictable,

627
00:35:53,971 --> 00:35:55,271
and I don't know
if I really need to see...

628
00:35:56,011 --> 00:35:58,841
the two of them living together
with my own eyes.

629
00:36:01,111 --> 00:36:04,021
Does Ju Ah's dad or his brother
know about this?

630
00:36:05,351 --> 00:36:07,721
I didn't tell them
since it's not for certain.

631
00:36:10,591 --> 00:36:12,361
I'll make time this weekend.

632
00:36:13,261 --> 00:36:14,731
We can go together, Mother.

633
00:36:18,701 --> 00:36:19,701
Mother.

634
00:36:22,201 --> 00:36:23,801
People live to be a hundred
these days.

635
00:36:24,301 --> 00:36:27,371
It's not about the last 30 years.
You still have another 30 to go.

636
00:36:27,911 --> 00:36:29,511
For the sake of
the rest of your life,

637
00:36:29,841 --> 00:36:31,981
you need to face this
and get closure.

638
00:36:49,131 --> 00:36:50,191
My gosh.

639
00:36:50,531 --> 00:36:51,631
Honey?

640
00:36:52,331 --> 00:36:54,071
Did you stay up all night?

641
00:36:54,931 --> 00:36:56,301
Gong Dae Han, that jerk.

642
00:36:57,231 --> 00:36:58,241
That traitor.

643
00:36:59,301 --> 00:37:02,241
I knew he wouldn't call.
You should've known better.

644
00:37:03,041 --> 00:37:04,041
I'm not letting him
get away with this.

645
00:37:13,051 --> 00:37:15,291
Father, where are you off to
so early?

646
00:37:16,321 --> 00:37:18,221
I'm going
to the medicinal herb market.

647
00:37:18,791 --> 00:37:20,391
You didn't mention it yesterday.

648
00:37:20,621 --> 00:37:22,591
I guess you weren't happy
with the quality of the herbs again.

649
00:37:25,131 --> 00:37:28,301
- I won't be late.
- Father! Eat something first.

650
00:37:28,371 --> 00:37:30,271
You didn't even eat dinner
last night.

651
00:37:31,071 --> 00:37:32,871
- I'm leaving.
- Wait, Father...

652
00:37:37,111 --> 00:37:38,881
Where did Grandma go
so early in the morning?

653
00:37:39,581 --> 00:37:42,481
She said she had to run an errand
at the Pharmacists' Association.

654
00:37:43,281 --> 00:37:45,751
Ju Ah, will you be
at the restaurant's grand opening?

655
00:37:45,821 --> 00:37:48,051
Yes, of course.
I'll be there with Director Yang.

656
00:37:48,491 --> 00:37:50,551
Hey, bring Jun Hyeok with you.

657
00:37:51,221 --> 00:37:54,091
- Gosh, no way.
- What? Why?

658
00:37:54,391 --> 00:37:55,561
Just bring him.

659
00:37:55,661 --> 00:37:56,931
Well...

660
00:37:57,461 --> 00:37:58,931
He's on a business trip today.

661
00:37:59,961 --> 00:38:02,231
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.
You're driving today.

662
00:38:02,401 --> 00:38:04,871
- What?
- Mom, you look really pale.

663
00:38:05,441 --> 00:38:07,671
What? You're right. Seong Mi.

664
00:38:08,211 --> 00:38:11,311
You look exhausted.
You've been pushing too hard.

665
00:38:11,781 --> 00:38:14,481
Hey, that's just what happens
when you get old, okay?

666
00:38:14,581 --> 00:38:17,881
At our age, it's normal to be tired.
Come on.

667
00:38:17,881 --> 00:38:19,551
- Dad, come on.
- Dad, seriously.

668
00:38:20,051 --> 00:38:21,751
What? No, I mean...

669
00:38:22,091 --> 00:38:24,691
I'm the one who's tired.
Gosh, I'm so tired. I'm exhausted.

670
00:38:24,761 --> 00:38:28,661
- Gosh, why am I so tired?
- I think I'll get an IV drip today.

671
00:38:29,161 --> 00:38:31,601
After you have some
of Dong Suk's barbecue today,

672
00:38:31,661 --> 00:38:33,801
you'll get your strength right back.

673
00:38:35,171 --> 00:38:38,341
One might think
it's your girlfriend's restaurant.

674
00:38:42,011 --> 00:38:44,011
I know, right? Why is he so excited?

675
00:38:51,251 --> 00:38:55,951
- You brought the photo, right?
- Yes. But it's very old.

676
00:38:56,451 --> 00:38:57,451
So is mine.

677
00:38:58,161 --> 00:38:59,221
Let's go.

678
00:39:08,471 --> 00:39:11,841
Now that we might actually meet him,
I'm getting cold feet.

679
00:39:16,941 --> 00:39:19,341
(Paos Eyewear)

680
00:39:20,911 --> 00:39:22,251
Oh, boy.

681
00:39:22,451 --> 00:39:25,921
You're showing 30-year-old photos
and asking if I've seen them...

682
00:39:25,981 --> 00:39:27,221
I'm afraid I don't recognize them.

683
00:39:28,451 --> 00:39:29,921
Right. I suppose that's fair.

684
00:39:29,921 --> 00:39:32,991
Excuse me. Someone saw him
getting glasses fitted here...

685
00:39:33,061 --> 00:39:34,091
not too long ago.

686
00:39:34,391 --> 00:39:39,161
- Let me check. Do you have a name?
- Gong Gi Cheol.

687
00:39:39,631 --> 00:39:41,171
Gong Gi Cheol...

688
00:39:42,171 --> 00:39:43,971
I don't have anyone
by that name here.

689
00:39:44,301 --> 00:39:46,671
Some people get prescribed glasses
without being added to our list,

690
00:39:46,741 --> 00:39:49,641
or they just buy
an off-the-shelf pair.

691
00:39:56,051 --> 00:39:57,681
Have you seen this man,
by any chance?

692
00:39:59,951 --> 00:40:01,321
Thank you.

693
00:40:02,351 --> 00:40:03,751
Excuse me, just a moment.

694
00:40:03,821 --> 00:40:07,461
Have you happened to see this man?

695
00:40:08,031 --> 00:40:09,031
Sorry, I don't recognize him.

696
00:40:12,601 --> 00:40:13,701
Listen.

697
00:40:14,571 --> 00:40:16,871
I guess the lady who saw him
was mistaken.

698
00:40:17,501 --> 00:40:19,841
If you're tired,
should we head back, sir?

699
00:40:21,811 --> 00:40:23,271
I think that would be for the best.

700
00:40:23,671 --> 00:40:24,681
Okay.

701
00:40:27,011 --> 00:40:30,551
- My goodness! Ms. Na.
- Oh, Mi Hyang! It's you!

702
00:40:30,811 --> 00:40:32,281
Wow, I can't believe
I'm seeing you here.

703
00:40:32,351 --> 00:40:34,921
I live here in Seongdam.

704
00:40:35,051 --> 00:40:37,961
Oh, really? I thought you said
you lived in Yongdugol.

705
00:40:39,021 --> 00:40:41,031
I moved a long time ago.

706
00:40:41,431 --> 00:40:45,561
As you know, I had my reasons,
so I couldn't really explain.

707
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:48,371
Oh, I see.

708
00:40:54,311 --> 00:40:57,471
My place is a mess,
so I can't invite you over.

709
00:40:57,471 --> 00:40:59,441
Oh, don't be silly.

710
00:40:59,711 --> 00:41:02,551
It's so good
to run into you like this.

711
00:41:04,011 --> 00:41:05,051
By the way,

712
00:41:05,451 --> 00:41:08,291
what brings you and Mr. Yang here?

713
00:41:09,751 --> 00:41:12,161
Well, someone...

714
00:41:12,821 --> 00:41:16,091
told me they saw
my husband around here.

715
00:41:18,801 --> 00:41:19,961
Dr. Gong?

716
00:41:21,601 --> 00:41:24,131
You haven't seen him,
have you, Mi Hyang?

717
00:41:24,571 --> 00:41:25,571
No.

718
00:41:26,241 --> 00:41:28,671
No, I mean... Gosh, if I had,

719
00:41:28,741 --> 00:41:30,741
I would have been
the first to call you.

720
00:41:31,981 --> 00:41:33,041
Of course.

721
00:41:33,341 --> 00:41:34,511
But...

722
00:41:35,611 --> 00:41:37,381
it's been so long,

723
00:41:38,251 --> 00:41:41,551
and my memory of his face is fading.

724
00:41:42,321 --> 00:41:44,521
It's been over 30 years,

725
00:41:46,461 --> 00:41:48,931
so I might not have recognized him
even if I saw him.

726
00:41:49,091 --> 00:41:52,601
Oh, I actually have a photo.

727
00:41:53,531 --> 00:41:55,531
This one's also
over 30 years old, though.

728
00:41:55,601 --> 00:41:56,601
Here.

729
00:42:03,041 --> 00:42:04,811
I wonder if this will help.

730
00:42:05,441 --> 00:42:07,481
He must look a lot older now.

731
00:42:09,681 --> 00:42:10,881
Yes, of course.

732
00:42:14,951 --> 00:42:16,721
Still, I'll see if I can find him.

733
00:42:18,121 --> 00:42:19,221
By the way,

734
00:42:19,561 --> 00:42:22,731
how's your brother doing?
Does he still have medicine?

735
00:42:22,791 --> 00:42:26,561
You gave me more than enough
when you thought you were moving.

736
00:42:27,001 --> 00:42:31,041
Come by anytime if you run out.
I'm not moving anymore, after all.

737
00:42:32,571 --> 00:42:36,271
That's such a relief.
I'll come see you soon.

738
00:42:37,171 --> 00:42:41,251
I've kept you long enough.
I should get going.

739
00:42:41,981 --> 00:42:45,321
I'll look for him
whenever I have a spare moment,

740
00:42:45,681 --> 00:42:49,551
and if I see anyone resembling him,
I'll call you right away.

741
00:42:51,161 --> 00:42:52,161
Thank you.

742
00:42:55,731 --> 00:42:56,791
Yes, Mother.

743
00:42:57,191 --> 00:43:01,201
You didn't call,
so I figured you couldn't find him.

744
00:43:02,131 --> 00:43:05,201
But I'm glad
you ran into someone you know.

745
00:43:05,841 --> 00:43:07,141
Did she say she'd help?

746
00:43:08,571 --> 00:43:09,771
No, wait.

747
00:43:12,581 --> 00:43:15,411
Okay. I'll meet you
at the BBQ place later.

748
00:43:16,251 --> 00:43:17,411
Okay, Mother.

749
00:43:19,321 --> 00:43:21,591
Still getting along so well
with your mother-in-law.

750
00:43:21,851 --> 00:43:24,821
I'm so jealous.
I'm still at war with mine.

751
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,361
I told you,
you should come in for a session.

752
00:43:26,461 --> 00:43:30,291
No, thanks. Some families are beyond
a prescription of love.

753
00:43:32,331 --> 00:43:34,031
You've got about ten minutes left.

754
00:43:34,231 --> 00:43:37,101
Can you speed it up?
My appointments are all backed up.

755
00:43:37,841 --> 00:43:39,571
I mean, I'm happy I got to see you,

756
00:43:39,671 --> 00:43:41,811
but why didn't you ask your husband
for an IV?

757
00:43:41,971 --> 00:43:45,211
You know what he said?
That it's because I'm getting old.

758
00:43:45,511 --> 00:43:49,111
He dotes on his patients
but is so mean to me.

759
00:43:49,311 --> 00:43:51,151
It's a terminal condition.

760
00:43:51,151 --> 00:43:54,151
Well, that's just how he is.
He's always been like that.

761
00:43:54,221 --> 00:43:58,391
- Mr. Fair-to-Everyone-Else.
- Right. He's always on their side.

762
00:44:00,761 --> 00:44:02,261
Let me draw some blood
before you go.

763
00:44:02,561 --> 00:44:05,201
Might as well run some tests
while you're here.

764
00:44:05,931 --> 00:44:06,931
Okay.

765
00:44:10,531 --> 00:44:11,871
Mi Hyang.

766
00:44:12,101 --> 00:44:15,271
I know you're busy,
so please don't go out of your way.

767
00:44:15,641 --> 00:44:18,311
Just give me a call
if you happen to run into him.

768
00:44:18,981 --> 00:44:20,181
Thank you.

769
00:44:24,851 --> 00:44:26,921
(Pharmacist)

770
00:44:48,311 --> 00:44:49,771
(Alterations)

771
00:44:49,771 --> 00:44:51,341
Welcome.

772
00:44:55,311 --> 00:44:58,621
Hey, how are
your new reading glasses?

773
00:45:15,171 --> 00:45:16,501
Is there anything you want to eat?

774
00:45:16,601 --> 00:45:19,841
I was just making a snack
for Ji Hu and me.

775
00:45:20,571 --> 00:45:24,681
I was going to make something,
but I was tired and took a nap.

776
00:45:25,911 --> 00:45:30,281
You seem to have your hands full.
I hear you'll be starting work soon.

777
00:45:30,481 --> 00:45:33,521
Tell me about it.
I'm busy with a million things.

778
00:45:34,451 --> 00:45:37,961
If you don't mind,
could I help you around the house?

779
00:45:38,021 --> 00:45:41,231
Nonsense. You're here to travel,
not to do housework.

780
00:45:41,891 --> 00:45:43,731
I've done enough traveling.

781
00:45:44,031 --> 00:45:47,361
There's one more person
I need to see before I go back.

782
00:45:48,431 --> 00:45:49,431
Who's that?

783
00:45:50,631 --> 00:45:51,671
Just someone.

784
00:45:52,841 --> 00:45:54,741
I hope you get to meet them.

785
00:45:54,911 --> 00:45:58,281
By the way, while you're here,
I'm your guardian,

786
00:45:58,411 --> 00:46:00,841
so if you need help with anything,
just let me know.

787
00:46:02,651 --> 00:46:07,121
You seem a bit different
from when I first met you, ma'am.

788
00:46:07,481 --> 00:46:10,491
What's with the "ma'am?"

789
00:46:10,621 --> 00:46:13,561
Honestly. Goodness,
you're Eun Bin's friend,

790
00:46:13,661 --> 00:46:15,461
so just call me Mom.

791
00:46:15,691 --> 00:46:18,861
Then you should drop the formalities
with me too, Mom.

792
00:46:20,301 --> 00:46:21,831
Really? All right, then.

793
00:46:23,171 --> 00:46:25,871
Speaking of which,
I wanted to ask you something.

794
00:46:27,101 --> 00:46:30,311
That time we first met,
what did you say to me in English?

795
00:46:30,441 --> 00:46:31,481
You were cursing me out,
weren't you?

796
00:46:32,841 --> 00:46:35,581
Would you like me
to teach you some English?

797
00:46:36,351 --> 00:46:38,581
My gosh, really? I would love that!

798
00:46:38,651 --> 00:46:42,491
My English is a little weak.
You'd think I'd be fluent.

799
00:46:42,551 --> 00:46:44,151
- Right?
- Yes.

800
00:46:44,961 --> 00:46:47,421
And once I start my business,
I'll have foreign customers.

801
00:46:47,791 --> 00:46:50,631
- I've been dying to learn.
- I can help you with that.

802
00:46:50,691 --> 00:46:53,461
Really? That's perfect. Thank you.

803
00:46:55,801 --> 00:46:58,401
Director Yang bought a ring for me?

804
00:46:58,471 --> 00:47:01,941
Yes. He's holding on to it
until your fathers make up.

805
00:47:02,011 --> 00:47:03,571
I think that's when he plans
to give it to you.

806
00:47:06,181 --> 00:47:08,181
Wait, you're funny.
Why would you tell me that?

807
00:47:08,411 --> 00:47:11,581
Director Yang wanted to surprise me.
Why would you go and spoil it?

808
00:47:12,951 --> 00:47:16,521
You're so naive.
You just don't get it, do you?

809
00:47:16,791 --> 00:47:20,891
Look, he bought it because
he's tired of the secrecy.

810
00:47:21,361 --> 00:47:23,861
I'm giving you a heads-up
so you can go and comfort him.

811
00:47:24,231 --> 00:47:25,231
I feel bad for the guy.

812
00:47:26,031 --> 00:47:27,401
Right.

813
00:47:30,231 --> 00:47:32,641
All right, so for our next meeting,

814
00:47:32,771 --> 00:47:35,571
I'd like each of you to come up with
concept ideas for the launch show.

815
00:47:35,811 --> 00:47:38,641
And please share the prep schedule
with Dr. Han Seong Mi.

816
00:47:38,881 --> 00:47:39,941
- Got it.
- Got it.

817
00:47:42,311 --> 00:47:43,581
Mr. Park.

818
00:47:44,051 --> 00:47:46,651
Would you be interested in seeing
the musical "Spark" this weekend?

819
00:47:47,221 --> 00:47:50,521
- Me?
- I have two extra tickets.

820
00:47:50,851 --> 00:47:54,691
- Double date with Ms. Gong?
- Yes!

821
00:47:55,161 --> 00:47:59,701
Come on, it's not like that.
We're like comrades, okay?

822
00:48:02,231 --> 00:48:04,501
Actually, we are dating.

823
00:48:05,471 --> 00:48:07,471
- What?
- What?

824
00:48:07,541 --> 00:48:12,011
But the thing is,
my boyfriend isn't Mr. Park.

825
00:48:13,041 --> 00:48:14,111
It's Director Yang.

826
00:48:15,251 --> 00:48:17,911
- What?
- Wait, really? Director Yang?

827
00:48:18,221 --> 00:48:20,851
But Director,
aren't you with the Vice President?

828
00:48:21,151 --> 00:48:25,561
- You didn't just dump her, did you?
- No, of course not. We...

829
00:48:25,821 --> 00:48:29,031
The Vice President and I are
only friends from school.

830
00:48:29,291 --> 00:48:30,561
And my girlfriend...

831
00:48:31,061 --> 00:48:32,061
is right here.

832
00:48:32,761 --> 00:48:34,831
- It is, in fact, Ms. Gong Ju Ah.
- What?

833
00:48:34,901 --> 00:48:36,871
- What?
- Since when?

834
00:48:36,931 --> 00:48:38,201
What are you saying, Director?

835
00:48:38,201 --> 00:48:39,801
- My gosh!
- So you two... You're really...

836
00:48:40,771 --> 00:48:44,011
- You're dating?
- So, you're a couple?

837
00:48:44,411 --> 00:48:46,781
- Give us a straight answer! What?
- Quiet down. Everyone, quiet.

838
00:48:48,551 --> 00:48:52,851
Mark my words.
If this leaves the Design Team,

839
00:48:52,921 --> 00:48:55,851
I'll hunt every one of you down
and make your life a living misery.

840
00:48:56,391 --> 00:48:57,391
Got it?

841
00:48:57,851 --> 00:49:00,491
There you have it. You heard her.
This stays between us.

842
00:49:04,761 --> 00:49:07,301
- What is going on? This is insane.
- Hey.

843
00:49:09,071 --> 00:49:10,071
Dismissed!

844
00:49:11,271 --> 00:49:12,701
Do you have any idea
when this started?

845
00:49:18,841 --> 00:49:21,481
I'm sorry for just blurting that out
without talking to you.

846
00:49:22,911 --> 00:49:26,221
For something like this,
you never need my permission.

847
00:49:26,621 --> 00:49:29,991
- Really?
- Of course! Hold me down.

848
00:49:30,051 --> 00:49:31,691
Otherwise, I might just float away.

849
00:49:32,661 --> 00:49:34,791
- You're that happy?
- Yes.

850
00:49:35,231 --> 00:49:37,561
But why did you decide
to tell everyone?

851
00:49:37,891 --> 00:49:39,861
I thought you hated the idea
of an office romance getting out.

852
00:49:40,861 --> 00:49:43,931
I don't know. I was tired
of people getting the wrong idea.

853
00:49:44,101 --> 00:49:46,671
And for once, I wanted
to be able to say it proudly.

854
00:49:47,041 --> 00:49:50,971
I wanted to brag about
what an amazing man I'm dating.

855
00:49:53,581 --> 00:49:56,051
But don't get too touched just yet.

856
00:49:56,381 --> 00:49:58,011
Why? Is there more?

857
00:49:58,721 --> 00:50:01,551
My dad says
he'll forgive your father.

858
00:50:01,851 --> 00:50:03,691
- For real?
- Yes.

859
00:50:09,831 --> 00:50:10,931
(Reserved)

860
00:50:12,631 --> 00:50:13,931
Is your whole family coming?

861
00:50:14,001 --> 00:50:16,371
- Yes. Is yours?
- Yes.

862
00:50:24,011 --> 00:50:25,611
What's up?

863
00:50:26,881 --> 00:50:30,481
Right now? Okay, I will.

864
00:50:35,651 --> 00:50:38,321
Hey, I'm just going to run out
and buy some wet wipes.

865
00:50:38,391 --> 00:50:42,031
- I'll go get them.
- No, it's okay. My aunt will go.

866
00:50:43,091 --> 00:50:44,461
- Why?
- Hush.

867
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:48,131
It's fine. I'll get them.
You two carry on.

868
00:50:50,001 --> 00:50:51,001
Be safe.

869
00:50:56,771 --> 00:50:58,781
- Mom.
- Yes?

870
00:50:58,841 --> 00:51:00,811
Did everything go well
at the Pharmacists' Association?

871
00:51:01,041 --> 00:51:03,181
What? Yes.

872
00:51:03,681 --> 00:51:07,051
Right. You're going to Dong Suk's
grand opening later, aren't you?

873
00:51:07,651 --> 00:51:09,351
- Of course, I am.
- All right.

874
00:51:09,921 --> 00:51:10,921
But Mom...

875
00:51:11,451 --> 00:51:12,821
Yes, what's up?

876
00:51:13,891 --> 00:51:16,231
Try not to be too surprised later.

877
00:51:16,791 --> 00:51:17,791
What?

878
00:51:18,361 --> 00:51:19,531
What...

879
00:51:20,161 --> 00:51:21,401
Is something surprising
going to happen?

880
00:51:22,031 --> 00:51:23,031
Yes, there's something.

881
00:51:23,401 --> 00:51:25,301
Come on, what is it?

882
00:51:26,741 --> 00:51:27,741
It's a secret.

883
00:51:30,971 --> 00:51:33,981
You're such a tease.

884
00:51:34,981 --> 00:51:35,981
Yes, please go on in.

885
00:51:36,051 --> 00:51:39,421
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

886
00:51:42,451 --> 00:51:43,491
Secret!

887
00:51:44,421 --> 00:51:45,421
Hey!

888
00:51:47,191 --> 00:51:48,991
- Hey.
- You got something to say to me?

889
00:51:49,461 --> 00:51:50,461
Can't say I do.

890
00:51:51,461 --> 00:51:52,501
Are you going to keep this up?

891
00:51:52,731 --> 00:51:57,001
I heard you have a pre-interview
for "Human Theater" today, right?

892
00:51:57,331 --> 00:51:59,141
You can hear about that
from my brother later.

893
00:51:59,501 --> 00:52:01,301
I'm running late,
so I have to go. Bye.

894
00:52:09,811 --> 00:52:10,811
Endorphin.

895
00:52:12,351 --> 00:52:13,351
Dorphin!

896
00:52:24,791 --> 00:52:25,801
I'm here.

897
00:52:28,431 --> 00:52:33,001
We're meeting later at the opening.
Is this to get our story straight?

898
00:52:34,041 --> 00:52:35,041
So our lips could meet.

899
00:52:35,141 --> 00:52:36,741
Are you crazy?

900
00:52:36,741 --> 00:52:39,211
It was about our story!
Is that why you called me?

901
00:52:39,211 --> 00:52:41,441
No, I told you
I had good news today, remember?

902
00:52:41,751 --> 00:52:42,911
Right. You were going to tell me,
weren't you?

903
00:52:42,981 --> 00:52:45,651
Yes. My brother said
he'll forgive your brother.

904
00:52:45,951 --> 00:52:47,681
They're going to meet today
and make up.

905
00:52:48,051 --> 00:52:49,891
- Really?
- Yes.

906
00:52:50,351 --> 00:52:53,761
So today, I'm going to stand up
before both our families and say it.

907
00:52:55,091 --> 00:52:57,891
I am in love with Yang Dong Suk.

908
00:53:00,131 --> 00:53:01,131
What?

909
00:53:01,501 --> 00:53:05,601
You promised to go out with me
if our families gave their blessing.

910
00:53:12,711 --> 00:53:14,041
Quick, hide!

911
00:53:16,051 --> 00:53:17,051
What? Why?

912
00:53:17,111 --> 00:53:20,121
Why is she walking so fast?
She's not a runner. My gosh.

913
00:53:20,421 --> 00:53:23,191
Auntie! Where did she go?

914
00:53:23,691 --> 00:53:26,491
My gosh. Where did she go now?

915
00:53:27,621 --> 00:53:30,031
Where could she have gone?
Seriously.

916
00:53:31,861 --> 00:53:35,631
Auntie!
My gosh, is that your boyfriend?

917
00:53:35,801 --> 00:53:38,971
Hello, there.
I'm her niece, Yang Eun Bin.

918
00:53:39,071 --> 00:53:40,641
- Aren't you going to say hi?
- Run!

919
00:53:40,641 --> 00:53:42,271
Who is he?

920
00:53:42,571 --> 00:53:46,681
Yang Dong Suk, you're so busted!
Hey, wait! Who are you?

921
00:53:47,011 --> 00:53:49,011
Who are you? Hey, you!

922
00:53:51,351 --> 00:53:52,351
Where?

923
00:53:53,751 --> 00:53:55,621
- Dong Suk, hide!
- Oh, no...

924
00:53:59,421 --> 00:54:02,431
- Where did they go?
- She's here!

925
00:54:03,931 --> 00:54:04,931
Unbelievable.

926
00:54:07,201 --> 00:54:08,571
She's gone. Quick, let's go.

927
00:54:10,471 --> 00:54:11,771
Come on, hurry up.

928
00:54:13,201 --> 00:54:14,201
Seriously.

929
00:54:15,111 --> 00:54:16,741
Where did they go?

930
00:54:19,311 --> 00:54:21,041
Hide.

931
00:54:27,121 --> 00:54:28,951
Hey, why are we running away?

932
00:54:29,621 --> 00:54:31,151
If Eun Bin finds out,
it'll get complicated.

933
00:54:31,621 --> 00:54:33,491
But what does it matter?
We're telling everyone later anyway.

934
00:54:34,521 --> 00:54:35,531
Are you really going to do it?

935
00:54:35,831 --> 00:54:36,831
Yes.

936
00:54:37,831 --> 00:54:39,331
I really can't hide it anymore.

937
00:54:40,561 --> 00:54:41,561
Hide what?

938
00:54:44,331 --> 00:54:45,341
My feelings for you.

939
00:55:29,381 --> 00:55:31,921
Wait, what?
They ran off holding hands?

940
00:55:32,351 --> 00:55:34,551
Oh, my gosh.
And you didn't even see who he was?

941
00:55:35,321 --> 00:55:36,851
That's a shame.

942
00:55:37,851 --> 00:55:38,861
But listen, Eun Bin...

943
00:55:39,361 --> 00:55:41,561
What about your bookstore job?
Why are you with your aunt?

944
00:55:42,731 --> 00:55:45,131
Oh, you got off early today?

945
00:55:46,361 --> 00:55:49,731
Okay. I'll get Ji Hu,
and we'll be right there. All right.

946
00:55:52,941 --> 00:55:54,941
Okay. Let's call it a day.

947
00:55:57,971 --> 00:56:00,041
But can I really just take it easy
and read the source material?

948
00:56:00,481 --> 00:56:02,781
I'm already so far behind
the other students.

949
00:56:03,781 --> 00:56:07,781
Studying under competitive pressure
isn't helpful at all.

950
00:56:08,221 --> 00:56:10,691
Let's try to have fun with it
and not think of it as studying.

951
00:56:11,551 --> 00:56:13,161
- Okay.
- Right.

952
00:56:14,961 --> 00:56:15,961
Yes.

953
00:56:20,601 --> 00:56:22,471
- Are you done?
- Yes, Aunt.

954
00:56:22,671 --> 00:56:26,941
- How's it going?
- Great. Ji Hu's a quick study.

955
00:56:27,041 --> 00:56:29,271
Once he gets his confidence up,
he'll improve in no time.

956
00:56:29,271 --> 00:56:31,671
Right. Ji Hu and I
have to get going.

957
00:56:31,941 --> 00:56:34,541
- Want to join us, Min Seo?
- No, I'm fine.

958
00:56:34,911 --> 00:56:36,511
It's a family thing.

959
00:56:36,981 --> 00:56:39,381
We're family if we live together,
and we're family if we eat together.

960
00:56:40,281 --> 00:56:41,351
Ji Hu's right.

961
00:56:42,121 --> 00:56:44,151
We're family.
So come with us, Min Seo.

962
00:56:44,951 --> 00:56:45,961
Okay.

963
00:56:54,531 --> 00:56:58,501
You're imagining telling your family
that we're dating, aren't you?

964
00:56:58,771 --> 00:57:01,201
Wow. How did you know?

965
00:57:02,541 --> 00:57:03,541
Don't even think about it.

966
00:57:03,811 --> 00:57:06,981
We have to sort out that whole mess
with Mr. Park and my family.

967
00:57:07,741 --> 00:57:10,881
I know. We just told the team today,

968
00:57:11,151 --> 00:57:14,751
- so wanting more would be greedy.
- Glad we're on the same page.

969
00:57:16,091 --> 00:57:19,561
Today, I'm going to sit
next to your dad and your uncle...

970
00:57:19,621 --> 00:57:21,361
and let them pour me drinks.

971
00:57:22,491 --> 00:57:25,361
I'm going to thank them
for forgiving my father...

972
00:57:25,701 --> 00:57:27,131
and express my gratitude personally.

973
00:57:27,501 --> 00:57:28,501
Good.

974
00:57:46,951 --> 00:57:47,951
You're here.

975
00:57:53,661 --> 00:57:54,661
You two...

976
00:57:55,291 --> 00:57:57,691
were meeting without me?

977
00:57:58,631 --> 00:58:00,001
I had something to discuss with him.

978
00:58:00,401 --> 00:58:01,401
What about?

979
00:58:02,071 --> 00:58:05,771
Is there some kind of problem?

980
00:58:06,701 --> 00:58:07,771
The thing is...

981
00:58:08,041 --> 00:58:10,311
While getting merchants' consent,
we heard about...

982
00:58:10,311 --> 00:58:13,941
the long-standing feud
between your families.

983
00:58:19,221 --> 00:58:20,221
And?

984
00:58:21,321 --> 00:58:23,891
So, the crew and I had a meeting,

985
00:58:24,321 --> 00:58:28,461
and since we place the highest value
on authenticity,

986
00:58:29,061 --> 00:58:32,131
the "lifelong friends" concept
just won't work.

987
00:58:32,931 --> 00:58:33,931
So?

988
00:58:34,831 --> 00:58:37,531
- So you're pulling the plug?
- No.

989
00:58:39,341 --> 00:58:40,801
We just need to change the concept.

990
00:58:41,141 --> 00:58:42,141
Change it...

991
00:58:42,971 --> 00:58:44,511
to what?

992
00:58:45,141 --> 00:58:47,881
We'll highlight Dr. Gong's family
as a long line of doctors,

993
00:58:47,941 --> 00:58:50,151
and pivot to a concept
of a harmonious family of doctors.

994
00:58:50,581 --> 00:58:52,451
We think a lot of viewers
would be curious...

995
00:58:52,521 --> 00:58:54,681
to see what Dr. Han's family
is like,

996
00:58:54,751 --> 00:58:56,091
so we think
the ratings would be great.

997
00:58:56,621 --> 00:59:01,361
Instead, you could appear in
the Merchants' Association episode.

998
00:59:01,421 --> 00:59:02,731
The optics would be
a bit better that way.

999
00:59:08,831 --> 00:59:09,831
I...

1000
00:59:10,401 --> 00:59:12,141
told you this wouldn't work.

1001
00:59:12,501 --> 00:59:13,601
What are we going to do?

1002
00:59:14,471 --> 00:59:16,011
He looks furious.

1003
00:59:17,371 --> 00:59:18,941
I'll talk to him.

1004
00:59:20,281 --> 00:59:22,011
Our two families have already
reconciled,

1005
00:59:22,281 --> 00:59:24,951
and I'll make sure there are
no issues with the broadcast.

1006
00:59:25,151 --> 00:59:27,481
So let's just stick
with the original concept.

1007
00:59:28,381 --> 00:59:29,451
Otherwise,

1008
00:59:30,221 --> 00:59:33,361
I'm pulling out, too.

1009
00:59:42,831 --> 00:59:44,831
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

1010
00:59:46,841 --> 00:59:50,241
Why are you drinking by yourself?
No one else is even here yet.

1011
00:59:53,311 --> 00:59:55,211
Seriously, what's gotten into you?

1012
00:59:56,951 --> 00:59:58,011
Did something happen?

1013
01:00:02,051 --> 01:00:03,691
That's ridiculous, right?

1014
01:00:04,491 --> 01:00:08,191
We agreed and signed a contract.
How can they change the concept now?

1015
01:00:08,391 --> 01:00:11,261
I know. That's why I told them
it was out of the question.

1016
01:00:12,431 --> 01:00:16,701
- Bucket must be furious.
- You have no idea.

1017
01:00:16,971 --> 01:00:20,641
I need to go calm him down. He just
stormed out without hearing me out.

1018
01:00:20,801 --> 01:00:21,801
- My gosh.
- Goodness.

1019
01:00:22,511 --> 01:00:23,871
Oh, Councilor Hwang.

1020
01:00:24,611 --> 01:00:26,441
- Dr. Gong.
- Yes.

1021
01:00:27,941 --> 01:00:29,251
What brings you to the market?

1022
01:00:30,181 --> 01:00:33,051
I was at the Onjeong Police Station
for a public safety meeting...

1023
01:00:33,521 --> 01:00:35,551
and thought I'd take a look
around the market.

1024
01:00:35,921 --> 01:00:37,051
I see.

1025
01:00:37,791 --> 01:00:41,361
By the way, this is my wife,
Dr. Han Seong Mi.

1026
01:00:42,991 --> 01:00:44,391
A pleasure to meet you.

1027
01:00:44,831 --> 01:00:46,431
I've heard so much about you.

1028
01:00:46,901 --> 01:00:48,561
I've heard great things
about you as well.

1029
01:00:55,241 --> 01:01:00,181
Councilor Hwang, you and Dr. Yang
should join me for dinner sometime.

1030
01:01:00,411 --> 01:01:01,411
Let's do that.

1031
01:01:02,041 --> 01:01:03,511
After hearing what you had to say,
Dr. Gong,

1032
01:01:03,981 --> 01:01:05,351
I've had a bit of a change of heart.

1033
01:01:06,221 --> 01:01:09,621
- Thank you, sir. We won't keep you.
- Take care.

1034
01:01:14,591 --> 01:01:16,661
- Fancy meeting him here.
- Tell me about it.

1035
01:01:17,261 --> 01:01:18,791
- Hey!
- Hey, you scared me.

1036
01:01:20,631 --> 01:01:22,471
Don't you think
you're going too far?

1037
01:01:22,801 --> 01:01:24,931
Hey, you're the one who stormed out
while I was talking.

1038
01:01:25,331 --> 01:01:26,671
When did you get so drunk?

1039
01:01:27,241 --> 01:01:28,701
What do you expect?

1040
01:01:29,771 --> 01:01:31,911
You're getting back at me,
aren't you?

1041
01:01:32,641 --> 01:01:34,441
I can't believe you.

1042
01:01:34,981 --> 01:01:37,481
I saved your life!

1043
01:01:37,981 --> 01:01:41,881
Dong Ik, what's gotten into you?
The family is coming. Stop it.

1044
01:01:41,981 --> 01:01:45,621
- Let's go inside and talk. Come on.
- Hey!

1045
01:01:45,891 --> 01:01:48,721
How can you get under my skin
like this?

1046
01:01:49,591 --> 01:01:51,861
Is this really what you wanted?

1047
01:01:52,461 --> 01:01:54,031
Oh, my.

1048
01:01:54,861 --> 01:01:56,231
Honey, what's wrong?

1049
01:01:56,571 --> 01:01:59,201
Se Ri,
this jerk stole Councilor Hwang...

1050
01:01:59,671 --> 01:02:03,471
- and "Human Theater" from me.
- It's a misunderstanding.

1051
01:02:03,541 --> 01:02:05,041
A misunderstanding?
I don't think so.

1052
01:02:05,681 --> 01:02:06,881
Hey, Gong Jeong Han. You...

1053
01:02:07,481 --> 01:02:09,781
You're trying to slowly destroy me,
aren't you?

1054
01:02:10,481 --> 01:02:13,781
Fine.
That video of my wife falling...

1055
01:02:14,321 --> 01:02:15,591
I'm the one who posted it!

1056
01:02:24,861 --> 01:02:28,301
- Hey, are you out of your mind?
- Honey!

1057
01:02:28,361 --> 01:02:30,001
Let me go.

1058
01:02:31,001 --> 01:02:33,601
I'm so frustrated I could burst!

1059
01:02:34,401 --> 01:02:37,941
- I'm going to tell them everything!
- Fine, go ahead.

1060
01:02:38,411 --> 01:02:39,781
Go on, spit it out.

1061
01:02:40,411 --> 01:02:42,781
What on earth are you talking about?

1062
01:03:15,711 --> 01:03:18,681
(Recipe For Love)

1063
01:03:19,781 --> 01:03:21,121
We've been caught.

1064
01:03:21,721 --> 01:03:23,351
What choice do we have?
We have to break up.

1065
01:03:23,421 --> 01:03:25,861
The infamous Pacu Nacho is going
to give up like this?

1066
01:03:26,221 --> 01:03:30,331
Since Dae Han has found someone new,
you don't need to worry about him.

1067
01:03:30,431 --> 01:03:32,131
Just focus on your own happiness.

1068
01:03:33,101 --> 01:03:35,031
So, our kiss changed your mind?

1069
01:03:35,031 --> 01:03:37,031
You don't care
if our brothers make up?

1070
01:03:38,171 --> 01:03:40,501
I have no intention
of making up whatsoever.

1071
01:03:41,171 --> 01:03:43,441
I'm really starting
to lose all hope.

1072
01:03:44,141 --> 01:03:45,541
Is he giving up on me?

1073
01:03:46,681 --> 01:03:47,741
Dong Suk, I'm sorry.

1074
01:03:48,638 --> 01:03:50,648
Dramaday.me
